HEADWORD: Lobeline
<hw>Lo*be"line</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A poisonous narcotic alkaloid extracted from the leaves of Indian
tobacco (<spn>Lobelia inflata</spn>) as a yellow oil, having a
tobaccolike taste and odor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

